  .row.slide.content-slide
    .col.s12 
      h2.heading Structure
    .col.s12.l6
      h4 Where do I put my slides HTML code?
      p Just put it inside the element with the calss <code>.main-container</code>

    .col.s12
      h4 How do I create a Slide
    .col.s12.l6
      p Every Slide must be a child of the <code>.main-container</code>. Each slide is at least 100% tall, but can get taller (then you can just simply scroll down). 
      p There are different kind of slides. To create a simple content slide with padding (like this one), use the class <code>.content-slide</code> like this:
      p Alternatively you can style them completely yourself.
    .col.s12.l6
      pre
        |<code>&lt;div class="slide content-slide">
        |   &lt;h2>Title&lt;/h2>
        |   &lt;p>Lorem ipsum...&lt;/p>
        |&lt;/div></code>


  .row.slide.content-slide
    .col.s12
      h2.heading Controls

    .col.s12.l6
      h4 Previous slide
      ul 
        li Pressing 
          span.key-list-up
        li Scrolling upwards beyond the slide start
        li pressing the "up" button (orange, top right)
    .col.s12.l6
      h4 Next slide
      ul 
        li Pressing 
          span.key-list-down
        li Scrolling down beyond the slide end
        li pressing the "down" button (orange, bottom right)
    .col.s12.margin-top
      h4 Number keys
      p You can also press the numbers 1 to 9 with one being the first, nine being the ninth (and zero being the tenth slide). 
      p.grey-text.text-darken-1 
        b Additional info:<br>
        |If you have n slides each number key k > n will scroll to page n instead of k. For example if you have only 4 pages, pressing 5 will bring you to page 4 (because 5 doesn't exist).
    .col.s12.margin-top
      h4 Scrolling in long slides or small displays
      p If the slide is larger than the display area, you either have to trim some fat or bite the bullet and scroll down while presentating... But be careful! if you scroll past the bottom of the slide you will be taken to the next slide.


